    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page, top-down narrative structure designed for recruiters. It starts with a strong hero section for immediate impact, followed by a 'Why Me for AIDocbuilder?' section that directly maps skills to the job description. The core of the application is a detailed, interactive 'Projects' section where key achievements are presented with metrics and visualizations. This is followed by 'Technical Skills' and 'Experience' sections for comprehensive detail. This linear, story-driven flow is chosen for its clarity and persuasive power, guiding the user through a compelling case for candidacy without requiring complex navigation. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Reduced asset production time by 40%. Goal: Showcase quantifiable impact. Viz/Presentation: Bar Chart (Chart.js). Interaction: Tooltips on hover to show data. Justification: A bar chart provides a clear, immediate visual comparison of 'before' and 'after,' making the 40% reduction instantly understandable. Library: Chart.js for its simplicity and responsiveness.
        - Report Info: Increased SaaS conversion by 22%. Goal: Demonstrate business impact. Viz/Presentation: Donut Chart (Chart.js). Interaction: Hover to highlight segments. Justification: A donut chart effectively visualizes a part-to-whole relationship, clearly showing the 22% increase in the context of the overall conversion metric. Library: Chart.js.
        - Report Info: Technical skills proficiency. Goal: Provide a quick, scannable overview of technical abilities. Viz/Presentation: Grouped lists with skill-level indicators (HTML/Tailwind). Interaction: None, designed for quick reading. Justification: A clean, organized list is more effective than a complex chart for conveying a wide range of qualitative skill information. Method: HTML/Tailwind.
        - Report Info: Project methodologies (e.g., AI-NPC system). Goal: Explain complex technical processes. Viz/Presentation: Structured text with highlighted keywords (HTML/Tailwind). Interaction: None. Justification: Clear, well-structured text is best for explaining nuanced technical workflows and architectures. Method: HTML/Tailwind.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
